&quot;Emilio Núñez (born Juan Emilio de la Caridad Núñez y Rodriguez on 27 December 1855 in Esperanza, Las Villas, Cuba - 5 May 1922 in Havana, Cuba) was a Cuban-American soldier, dentist, and politician.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emilio_N%c3%ba%c3%b1ez" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emilio_N%C3%BA%C3%B1ez</a>

See e.g.
<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn92053934/1912-01-22/ed-1/seq-1/" rel="nofollow">Rock Island Argus., January 22, 1912, Image 1</a>, last column, with photo: &quot;GEN. NUNEZ CAUSES TROUBLES IN CUBA&quot;
<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85042242/1913-04-27/ed-1/seq-1/" rel="nofollow">Bismarck daily tribune., April 27, 1913, Image 1</a>, with photo: &quot;NEW SECRETARY OF AGRICULTURE IN CUBA IS TOBACCO GROWER&quot;

The <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045211/1914-09-22/ed-2/seq-11/" rel="nofollow">Evening public ledger., September 22, 1914, Postscript Edition, Page 11</a>, first column described him as &quot; the most powerful member of the present Cuban Cabinet and President Menocal's principal
advisor&quot;
